text: Is ANYONE asking how Ron DeSantis was worth $340,000 in 2020 and is now worth $52 million? 🤔

gpt.summary: The claim that Ron DeSantis was worth $340,000 in 2020 and is now worth $52 million is misleading and factually incorrect. Therefore, the significant financial increase suggested in the tweet is not supported by credible evidence (https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2022/may/12/tweets/tweets-conflate-ron-desantis-massive-campaign-fund/, https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/753508-ron-desantis-net-worth)

text:
The Biden administration is banning Juuls but distributing free crack pipes. 

Make it make sense.

gpt.summary: The claim that the Biden administration is distributing free crack pipes is misleading. Both the White House and Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) have clarified that federal funds are not used to distribute crack pipes within safe smoking kits. These kits are part of harm reduction strategies and may include items like alcohol swabs, lip balm, and materials to promote hygiene but not pipes. The initiative focuses on reducing harm from drug use, such as preventing the spread of diseases like HIV and hepatitis, rather than promoting drug use (https://www.factcheck.org/2022/02/biden-initiative-funds-drug-overdose-prevention-not-crack-pipes/, https://truthout.org/articles/no-biden-is-not-handing-out-crack-pipes-heres-why-activists-do/)

community_notes.summary: Biden Initiative Funds Drug Overdose Prevention, Not ‘Crack Pipes’ https://www.factcheck.org/2022/02/biden-initiative-funds-drug-overdose-prevention-not-crack-pipes/

text: Americans will have to apply for a visa to go to Europe starting next year: Online application (including biometric information, work experience, medical conditions, and initial itinerary).

gpt.summary: The statement about Americans needing to apply for a visa to go to Europe starting next year is misleading. The requirement is actually for an ETIAS travel authorisation, not a visa, and it starts in mid-2025. ETIAS is a travel authorization for visa-exempt countries entering Europe. (https://travel-europe.europa.eu/etias_en)

community_notes.summary: Americans will not need a visa, they will however need to provide information before they fly to the EU. This program is called ETIAS: https://travel-europe.europa.eu/etias_en    America has a similar process called ESTA for people coming to the US. It includes asking parents names and your social media accounts: https://www.nnuimmigration.com/esta-questions/

text:
Biden won 477 counties
Trump won 2,497 counties

Who do you think won the election?

Something isn’t adding up.

gpt.summary: The statement about the number of counties won by each candidate in the 2020 presidential election lacks important context. The U.S. presidential elections are determined by the Electoral College, not the total number of counties won. Joe Biden won the election with 306 electoral votes to Donald Trump's 232, and Biden also received the majority of the popular vote, with over 81 million votes compared to Trump's 74 million (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_United_States_presidential_election, https://brilliantmaps.com/2020-county-election-map/, https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2021/06/30/behind-bidens-2020-victory/)

community_notes.summary: Loving County, Texas has 64 inhabitants. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loving_County,_Texas    Los Angeles County, California has nearly 10 million inhabitants, about 150,000 times as many. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles_County,_California    The American system provides one vote per eligible voter, not one vote per county. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_man,_one_vote

text: Don’t you find it odd that women in America are being treated worse than women in Afghanistan?  We wasted 2trillion dollars plus to go into Afghanistan to liberate their women and children?  Something ain’t right here folks. Are you catching on yet?

gpt.summary: The claim that women in America are being treated worse than women in Afghanistan lacks important context and misrepresents the situation in both countries. In Afghanistan, since the Taliban takeover in August 2021, women and girls face severe restrictions on their rights, including bans on education beyond the sixth grade and on working outside specific sectors. The UN and other international bodies have documented these restrictions and their impact on Afghan women's freedom and well-being (https://www.unwomen.org/en/digital-library/publications/2021/12/gender-alert-womens-rights-in-afghanistan, https://www.ohchr.org/en/press-releases/2023/03/afghanistan-un-experts-say-20-years-progress-women-and-girls-rights-erased, https://www.unwomen.org/en/news-stories/feature-story/2023/08/women-in-afghanistan-from-almost-everywhere-to-almost-nowhere, https://news.un.org/en/story/2023/03/1134352). . While the United States has made progress towards gender equality, significant challenges remain, with a majority of Americans believing more efforts are needed to achieve gender equality (https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2020/07/07/a-century-after-women-gained-the-right-to-vote-majority-of-americans-see-work-to-do-on-gender-equality/). However, comparing the two directly overlooks the critical differences in the nature and extent of restrictions on women's rights and freedoms in each context.

community_notes.summary: Women in Afghanistan are in great peril. This kind of divisive language is misleading and demonstrably incorrect.    https://www.latintimes.com/woman-recalls-being-shot-eyes-gouged-out-brutal-torture-taliban-urges-women-join-482016    https://www.wsj.com/articles/afghans-tell-of-executions-forced-marriages-in-taliban-held-areas-11628780820    https://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-rights-women/invisible-taliban-child-brides-widows-trapped-as-sex-slaves-idUSKCN1B31PL

text: Many people have been asking me how I got myocarditis despite being unvaccinated. Two days after spending time with a friend who had just received the vaccine, my heart began to have severe irregularities, and it took me a year to recover. Vaccine shedding is a valid concern.

gpt.summary: Myocarditis can be caused by a variety of factors including infections (like viruses or bacteria), autoimmune diseases, and environmental toxins, not solely through vaccination. There is no current scientific evidence to support the claim that 'vaccine shedding' from vaccinated individuals can cause myocarditis in unvaccinated individuals (https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/myocarditis/symptoms-causes/syc-20352539, https://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/heart-inflammation/myocarditis, https://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/health/conditions-and-diseases/myocarditis)

community_notes.summary: Myocarditis is a known symptom of Covid-19 and is far more common than any reaction to the vaccine.   https://www.heart.org/en/news/2022/08/22/covid-19-infection-poses-higher-risk-for-myocarditis-than-vaccines
